rbvs.product

Class CompositeProduct

  • java.lang.Object
    • rbvs.product.Product
      • rbvs.product.CompositeProduct
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDeepCopy, IProduct

    public class CompositeProduct
extends Product
    Provides the means to specify a Composite-Product that is a collection of products. Composite-Products have, besides a name and a discount, a list of Products. A Composite-Product can define a discount that is applied when calculating the total price. The price of the Composite-Product is specified by the list of products contained in the Composite-Product and the given discount.

    Attributes of the class:

    • discount percentage (as a point number)
    • list of Products

    • Constructor Detail

      • CompositeProduct

        public CompositeProduct(String name,
                        float discountPercentage)
        Constructor that takes two arguments (name and discount) and initializes the product. The price is initialized with zero. If the passed name is NULL the product name will be initialized with an empty string. If the passed discount is below zero the discount is set to zero. In case of a passed discount above 100 the discount is set to 100. If the discount is between zero and 100 percent the Composite-Product is initialized accordingly.
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the product
        discountPercentage - the discount as a percentage

      • CompositeProduct

        public CompositeProduct(String name,
                        float discountPercentage,
                        Collection<Product> products)
        Constructor that takes three arguments (name, discount and a list of products) and initializes the product.

        product name: If the passed name is NULL the product name will be initialized with an empty string.

        discount: If the discount is between zero and 100 percent the Composite-Product is initialized accordingly. If the passed discount is below zero percent the discount is set to zero. In case of a discount above 100 percent the discount is initialized with 100 percent.

        products: If the list of products is not null, the given products will be added to the product list of this Composite-Product.

        Parameters:
        name - the name of the product
        discountPercentage - the discount
        products - the products that should be associated with this Composite-Product

      • deepCopy

        public CompositeProduct deepCopy()
        Creates and returns a copy of this object by either invoking a private copy constructor, or by creating a new object of the same class and setting its values accordingly. The precise meaning of "copy" may depend on the class of the object. The general intent is that, for any object x, the expression: 
         x.deepCopy() != x
        will be true, and that the expression: 
         x.deepCopy().getClass() == x.getClass()
        will be true, but these are not absolute requirements.

        While it is typically the case that: 

         x.deepCopy().equals(x)
        will be true, this is not an absolute requirement.

        NOTE: Keep in mind that for all referenced Products in this CompositeProduct, e.g. the elements of the private Collection, a copy has to be created as well.

        deepCopy in interface IDeepCopy
